FAQs: Charles University Faculty of Medicine in Hradec Kralove
What programs are offered at the Charles University Faculty of Medicine in Hradec Kralove?
The Charles University Faculty of Medicine in Hradec Kralove offers a range of programs, including a six-year General Medicine program and a six-year Dentistry program for undergraduate students. Additionally, there are various postgraduate programs, including PhD programs in biomedical sciences and specialized medical training.

Is the General Medicine program at the Charles University Faculty of Medicine in Hradec Kralove taught in English?
Yes, the General Medicine program at the Charles University Faculty of Medicine in Hradec Kralove is taught in English, making it accessible to international students who are proficient in English.

What are the admission requirements for the Charles University Faculty of Medicine in Hradec Kralove?
Admission requirements typically include a high school diploma with good grades in science subjects (Biology, Chemistry, Physics), proficiency in English (IELTS or TOEFL scores may be required), and successful completion of the entrance examination conducted by the faculty.
